  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You can attempt to fascinate another creature for 1 minute with the movement of your plumage using an action, to avoid it, the target creature must pass a Charisma saving throw with DC equal to 8 + your Charisma modifier + your proficiency bonus. If the save fails, the target sees the caster as a person they trust and love. Non-intelligent creatures are not affected. The target responds appropriately, following the caster around as long as this doesn't pose a risk to their safety. The fascinated condition also ends if the target becomes aggressive towards the fascinated creature. This ability can be used again after finishing a short rest.</p>",
